Is this trial going to result in me being sentenced to three days of solitary confinement, even if the jury unanimously votes not guilty? (Oh, but wait. I think Mario ate that one guy's lunch, so he's going to get at least one guilty vote.)

Aw, Mokou missed the party? Oh, you should've been there! There was this one moment where DK was leading by five stars near the end of a game, but then Wario landed on a "Chance Time" space on the last turn and caused all of DK's stars to be given to Luigi, who had none at the time! DK was not amused, to say the least!
So, all of a sudden, we've got seven new levels to play! Oh, wow... And I thought I was done with this hack for a moment!

Well, the next hit after the screen dimmed ended that pattern, so no seizures right now. Also, this pattern is generous with the power ups. Make sure to grab them slowly enough so that I don't get gypped!

Okay, it looks like I have to use those weird red things now. The type of jump I'll want to use depends on whether they'll be "stabby" or not when I land on them. (If I'm unsure, I should spin jump, so that I don't take damage for being wrong.)
I love how Mario says, "Oh, hi Keine!" there!
Okay, here I get blindsided by Mokou right out the door, but aside from that, as long as those evil homing bullets don't show up again, this one should be simple.

I don't think I've encountered a custom sprite quite like this one before! However, I can spin jump off them, so that's one thing I can do to reach Keine. (I can also make use of the random bullet generator too.)
Ack! They're attacking me from below here! Quick, just grab the springboard (which I'm sure I'll need) and run!
